      <species metaid="metaid_83" sboTerm="SBO:0000253" id="species_139848" name="P2X purinoreceptors:ATP [plasma membrane]" compartment="compartment_876" initialAmount="0" hasOnlySubstanceUnits="false" boundaryCondition="false" constant="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Derived from a Reactome Complex. Here is Reactomes nested structure for this complex: (30616, Q99572, Q9UBL9, O15547, P56373, P51575, Q99571, Q93086). Reactome uses a nested structure for complexes, which cannot be fully represented in SBML Level 3 Version 1 core</p>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">P2X1 protein readily forms stable trimers and hexamers, suggesting that the intact receptor is a multimer of three or six subunits in heterologous expression systems. However,assembly in native cells may be influenced significantly by associated proteins that are not present in heterologous expression systems.</p>
