      <species metaid="metaid_220" sboTerm="SBO:0000253" id="species_139933" name="fibrin multimer [extracellular region]" compartment="compartment_984" initialAmount="0" hasOnlySubstanceUnits="false" boundaryCondition="false" constant="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Derived from a Reactome Complex. Here is Reactomes nested structure for this complex: (6xP02679, 6xP02671, 6xP02675). Reactome uses a nested structure for complexes, which cannot be fully represented in SBML Level 3 Version 1 core</p>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The fibrin &quot;monomers&quot; formed by the action of thrombin on fibrinogen associate spontaneously into multimers. This association can follow several distinct pathways and may be able to form several types of higher-order structures. All of these possibilities are represented in Reactome as a fibrin trimer.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
