      <species metaid="metaid_668" sboTerm="SBO:0000253" id="species_418167" name="F2R:ARRB2 [plasma membrane]" compartment="compartment_876" initialAmount="0" hasOnlySubstanceUnits="false" boundaryCondition="false" constant="false">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Derived from a Reactome Complex. Here is Reactomes nested structure for this complex: (P25116, P32121). Reactome uses a nested structure for complexes, which cannot be fully represented in SBML Level 3 Version 1 core</p>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Following receptor activation, PAR1 complexes with beta-arrestin. Beta-arrestins are adaptor proteins that play a central role in GPCR desensitization and internalization, and also act as scaffolds for the formation of signalling complexes that are independent of G-protein signalling.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="#metaid_668">
              <bqbiol:is>
                <rdf:Bag>
                  <rdf:li rdf:resource="https://identifiers.org/reactome:R-HSA-418167"/>
                </rdf:Bag>
              </bqbiol:is>
              <bqbiol:hasPart>
                <rdf:Bag>
