      <reaction metaid="metaid_766" id="reaction_210304" name="Interaction of integrin alphaVbeta3 with PECAM1" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Alpha v beta 3 integrin is one of the potential heterophilic ligands of PECAM-1 that is involved in down-regulation of T-cell responses. The heterophilic interaction of alpha v beta 3 integrin on endothelial cells with PEACAM-1 on leukocytes increases the adhesive function of beta integrins on T cells, monocytes, neutrophils and NK cells suggesting that leukocyte PEACAM-1 act as a signaling molecule.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
