      <reaction metaid="metaid_767" id="reaction_202704" name="Integrin alphaXbeta2 binds JAM3" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Although JAM-C is better known for its interaction with MAC-1, an interaction with CD11c/CD18 (known as alpha X beta 2), has also been described.</p>
