      <reaction metaid="metaid_778" id="reaction_377640" name="Autophosphorylation of SRC" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_70101">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Clustering of Integrin alphaIIb beta3 complexes results in the trans auto-phosphorylation of SRC tyrosine residue 419 (often referred to as 418 in the literature, as the initiating methionine is cleaved in the mature peptide) in SRC&apos;s kinase activation loop.</p>
        </notes>
