      <reaction metaid="metaid_782" id="reaction_9932945" name="SERPINA10 binds PROZ" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_984">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">This Reactome event shows the interaction between Protein Z (PROZ) and Z-dependent protease inhibitor (ZPI or SERPINA10).PROZ, a vitamin K-dependent cofactor, enhances the inhibition of membrane-associated factor Xa (FXa) by ZPI, encoded by the SERPINA10 gene (Huang X et al., 2008, 2010, 2019). In plasma, PROZ circulates bound to ZPI (SERPINA10) (Tabatabai A et al., 2001). Structural and kinetic studies revieled that PROZ tightly binds SERPINA10 through ionic and hydrophobic interactions with Kd values in the nanomolar range (Wei Z et al., 2009; Huang X et al., 2010, 2015). The interaction between PROZ and SERPINA10 is mediated by binding of the PROZ&apos;s C-terminal pseudo-catalytic domain to charged surfaced residues of SERPINA10 (Rezaie AR et al., 2008; Huang X et al., 2010; Qureshi SH et al., 2014). The epidermal growth factor-like domain 2 (EGF2) of PROZ may also contribute to the binding to SERPINA10 (Qureshi SH et al., 2014; Huang X et al., 2012). SERPINA10 is also activated by heparin inducing conformational changes that antagonize PROZ binding (Huang X et al., 2022).</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
