      <reaction metaid="metaid_794" id="reaction_437195" name="PDPK1 activates PRKCZ" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_70101">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">3-phosphoinositide dependent protein kinase-1 (Pdpk1, also known as Pdk1 and PKB kinase because of its activity at Protein kinase B) phosphorylates T410 of protein kinase C zeta type (Prkcz, also known as PKC zeta), leading to activation. The motif surrounding T410 is highly conserved in other PKC family members suggesting that Pdpk1 might activate other PKCs.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
