      <reaction metaid="metaid_797" id="reaction_377643" name="Dephosphorylation of inactive SRC by PTPB1" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_70101">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The integrin alphaIIb beta3:Inactive SRC complex recruits PTP1B protein tyrosine phosphatase resulting in the dephosphorylation of SRC tyrosine 530. The phosphorylated tail of SRC tail interacts with the SH2 domain thereby repressing kinase activity; removal of phosphorylation activates SRC kinase activity.</p>
        </notes>
