      <reaction metaid="metaid_798" id="reaction_202721" name="JAM2 binds JAM3" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">JAM2 and JAM3 bind each other and are strongly expressed by endothelial cells of high endothelial venules, the predominant site of leukocyte extravasation. JAM2 and JAM3 also bind to the leukocyte integrins VLA-4 and Mac-1 respectively.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
