      <reaction metaid="metaid_808" id="reaction_419490" name="Binding of ATP to P2X receptors" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_984">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">P2X receptors are a family of cation-permeable ligand gated ion channels that open in response to the binding of extracellular adenosine triphosphate (ATP) (Gicquel et al. 2015). All members of the family are thought to be functionally trimeric.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
