      <reaction metaid="metaid_811" id="reaction_994020" name="IRF1 binds the promoters of Interferon alpha and beta" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_7660">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Interferon regulatory factor-1 (IRF-1) is a positive transcription factor for genes involved in immune response, cell growth regulation and apoptosis in mammalian cells. Many agents such as viruses, interferon (IFN), double-stranded RNA (dsRNA), and proinflammatory cytokines induce IRF-1 transcription. IRF-1 transcriptionally activates many IRF-1-regulated genes during normal physiological and pathological conditions, including interferon-beta and alpha (Escalante et al. 1998, Harada et al. 1990), iNOS, COX-2, VCAM-1, IL-12, IL-15, CIITA, Caspase-1 and Caspase-7 (Upreti and Rath 2005).</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
            <rdf:Description rdf:about="#metaid_811">
              <dc:creator>
                <rdf:Bag>
                  <rdf:li rdf:parseType="Resource">
                    <vCard:N rdf:parseType="Resource">
                      <vCard:Family>Jupe</vCard:Family>
                      <vCard:Given>Steve</vCard:Given>
                    </vCard:N>
                  </rdf:li>
                  <rdf:li rdf:parseType="Resource">
                    <vCard:N rdf:parseType="Resource">
                      <vCard:Family>Akkerman</vCard:Family>
                      <vCard:Given>Jan Willem N</vCard:Given>
