      <reaction metaid="metaid_820" id="reaction_443905" name="SHC1 bound to integrin alphaIIb beta3 is phosphorylated somehow" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">In a mechanism that is presumed to be analagous to signaling of SHC downstream of the insulin and TrkA receptors, SHC becomes phosphorylated and dissociates from the integrin alphaIIb beta3 complex.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
