      <reaction metaid="metaid_825" id="reaction_202702" name="CD177 binds PECAM-1" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">CD177 is a 58- to 64-kDa glycosylphosphatidylinositol-anchored glycoprotein expressed exclusively by neutrophils, neutrophilic metamyelocytes, and myelocytes, but not by any other blood cells. It has been shown that neutrophil-specific CD177 is a heterophilic binding partner of PECAM-1, constituting a novel pathway that promotes neutrophil transmigration.</p>
        </notes>
