      <reaction metaid="metaid_841" id="reaction_9929060" name="TF:FVII:FXa -&gt;TF:FVIIa:FXa (FXa catalyst) " reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_984">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Upon vessel damage, tissue factor (TF), factor VII (FVII), and FX form a ternary complex (Riewald M and Ruf W 2001; Norledge BV et al., 2003; Venkateswarlu D et al., 2003; reviewed in Lee CJ et al., 2010; Vadivel K and Bajaj SP 2012). Within this complex, FVII and FX reciprocally activate each other via proteolytic cleavage generating activated FVIIa and FXa. Once activated, FXa can remain associated with TF:FVII or may dissociate from TF:VII:FXa and TF:VIIa:FXa (Norledge BV et al., 2003; Venkateswarlu D et al., 2003).This Reactome event shows the release of FXa from the TF:FVII:FXa complex. When released, soluble FXa binds to factor V (FV). The resulting prothrombinase FXa:FVa complex cleaves prothrombin (factor II) to thrombin (factor IIa), a key enzyme that further catalyzes the conversion of fibrinogen to fibrin, leading to the formation of a stable blood clot.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
