      <reaction metaid="metaid_846" id="reaction_204500" name="CyP60 chaperones Basigin" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_20699">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Basigin serves as a signaling receptor for extracellular cyclophilins. Its been reported that cyclophilin 60 (Cyp60), a distinct member of the cyclophilin family is involved in the regulation of intracellular transport of basigin. The mechanism of this activity involves interaction of Cyp60 with the proline-containing region within or adjacent to the predicted transmembrane domain basigin. Cyp60 is co-localized with basigin at the plasma membrane suggesting that Cyp60 may function as a chaperone escorting basigin through the secretory pathway.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
