      <reaction metaid="metaid_853" id="reaction_481009" name="Exocytosis of platelet dense granule content" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">ADP is the most important constituent of dense granules, essential for recruiting platelets to the site of vascular injury. Other components include ATP, Ca++, GDP, GTP, Mg++, orthophospate, pyrophosphate, and serotonin.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
