      <reaction metaid="metaid_860" id="reaction_442291" name="VAV2 is a GEF for Rho/Rac family kinases" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_70101">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Members of the Vav family are guanine nucleotide exchange factors (GEFs) for Rho-family GTPases. Vav2 is a GEF for RhoA, RhoB and RhoG, and possibly Rac1 and Cdc42</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
