      <reaction metaid="metaid_864" id="reaction_139842" name="Binding of Syk tyrosine kinase" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_70101">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Syk binds to the phosphorylated ITAM motif of Fc epsilon R1 gamma chain, each SH2 domain binding a phosphorylated tyrosine. Unlike Zap70, Syk appears to autophosphorylate, so does not require Src family kinases for activation.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
