      <reaction metaid="metaid_877" id="reaction_375133" name="Basigin binds Mannose-carrying cell recognition molecules" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Based on in vitro affinity chromatography study, basigin was found to bind to high mannose-carrying cell recognition molecules, such as myelin-associated glycoprotein, L1 and the beta2-subunit of Na+/K+-ATPase.</p>
        </notes>
