      <reaction metaid="metaid_884" id="reaction_437932" name="p-Y348-SYK binds VAV family" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_70101">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The SH2 region of Vav1 binds to Syk at a site including phosphorylated tyrosine Y348. Mutation of this residue to F abolishes binding and subsequent Vav1 phosphorylation. Vav2 has also been shown to bind Syk.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
