      <reaction metaid="metaid_886" id="reaction_434633" name="PIP2 binds inhibiting VAV" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_70101">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Vav interacts directly with PIP2 and PIP3, with a fivefold selectivity for PIP3 over PIP2. PIP3 gives a twofold stimulation of Vav1 GEF activity while PIP2 leads to 90% inhibition. Binding probably occurs through the PH domain, known to bind phosphoinositides.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
