      <reaction metaid="metaid_898" id="reaction_5694462" name="ABHD6,12 hydrolyse 3AG" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Three members of the serine hydrolase family are involved in the degradation of the endocannabinoid 2-arachidonoylyglycerol (C20:4) (2AG). The major enzymatic route for 2AG inactivation is via hydrolysis, generating arachidonic acid (AA) and glycerol. Two of the serine hydrolases, monoacylglycerol lipases 6 and 12 (ABHD6 and 12), have preference for the 3-acyl isomer of arachidonoylyglycerol (3AG) although they can also hydrolyse 2AG at a lower rate (Navia-Paldanius et al. 2012, Savinainen et al. 2012).</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
