      <reaction metaid="metaid_909" id="reaction_375131" name="Basigin binds CD98 complex" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">CD97hc is a multifunctional glycoprotein with a single transmembrane domain, is highly expressed on proliferating cells, and functions as a chaperone for transporters. CD98hc forms disulfide-bonded heterodimers with at least seven different light chains (SLC7A5-11) that serve as amino acid transporters. Covalent cross-linking, mass spectrometric protein identification, and co-immunoprecipitation shows selective CD147 association with CD98hc complex.</p>
        </notes>
