      <reaction metaid="metaid_915" id="reaction_432110" name="Integrin alpha IIb beta3 T779 phosphorylation blocks SHC binding" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The binding of SHC to integrin alpha IIb beta 3 is blocked by phosphorylation of beta 3 at Thr-779, or by substitution of this residue for Asp. PDK1 and Akt1/PKB-alpha both specifically target Thr-779 in in vitro assays.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
