      <reaction metaid="metaid_940" id="reaction_202727" name="Integrin alphaMbeta2 (MAC1) binds JAM3" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Recruitment of monocytic cells to the vessel wall by platelets is mediated via CD11b/CD18 (Mac-1) and platelet JAM-C. In the case of dendritic cells, this interaction leads to their activation and platelet phagocytosis. This process may be of importance for progression of atherosclerotic lesions.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
