      <reaction metaid="metaid_944" id="reaction_372705" name="Recruitment of BCAR1 to PTK2 complex" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_70101">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">BCAR1 (breast cancer anti-estrogen resistance protein1, also known as Crk-associated substrate (Cas) or p130Cas) is an adaptor protein that promotes protein-protein interactions, leading to the multiprotein complexes. The interaction of ?BCAR1/p130Cas with other proteins modulates cell motility, survial and proliferation. BCAR1/P130Cas is one of the main phosphorylation targets of the PTK2/SRC complex. The BCAR1 SH3 domain binds to PR1 and PR2 (‘PxxP’) domains in the PTK2 C-terminal domain.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
