      <reaction metaid="metaid_946" id="reaction_202714" name="CD58 binds CD2" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The crystal structure of the human CD2-CD58 complex also shows that most of the residues at the interface between these two proteins are charged and form several inter-protein salt bridges.</p>
        </notes>
