      <reaction metaid="metaid_954" id="reaction_429497" name="SLP-76 stimulates PLC gamma 2" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">SLP-76 has a well-established role in recruitment of PLC gamma 1 in immunoreceptor signalling; its role in the recruitment of PLC gamma 2 in integrin signalling is less clear. Results from SLP-76 null mice imply a functional role in GPVI signalling. Platelets from SLP-76 null mice exhibit a marked reduction in spreading and a decrease in whole cell phosphotyrosine levels when adhered to a fibrinogen-coated surface. In vivo reconstitution of SLP-76 by retroviral gene transfer corrects bleeding diathesis and restores normal responses to both collagen and fibrinogen (Judd et al., 2000).</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
