      <reaction metaid="metaid_969" id="reaction_434798" name="CRAC translocates calcium from the extracellular region to the cytosol" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Activation of Calcium-release-activated (CRAC) channels allows influx of calcium. The Orai component of CRAC is responsible for the selectivity of the channel, while the Stim component is responsible for activation.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
