      <reaction metaid="metaid_979" id="reaction_5604929" name="Activated protein C binds Protein S" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_984">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Activated protein C binds to Protein S on appropriate cell surfaces where it inactivates factors Va and VIIIa. Protein S is best known as a cofactor for the Activated protein C (APC)-catalyzed inactivation of factor Va (Walker 1980). Protein S must be membrane-bound to display this cofactor activity (Hackeng et al. 1993). Protein S binding brings the active site of APC closer to the phospholipid cell surface (Yegneswaran et al. 1999).</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
