      <reaction metaid="metaid_985" id="reaction_8858428" name="FCAMR binds IgA" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">IgA nephropathy (IgAN), the most common glomerulonephritis, is characterized by the deposition of IgA immune complexes in the glomerular mesangium. This is the result of High affinity immunoglobulin alpha and immunoglobulin mu Fc receptor (FCAMR, CD351) binding to IgA (McDonald et al. 2002).</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
