      <reaction metaid="metaid_987" id="reaction_429415" name="SYK binds to integrin alphaIIb beta3" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_70101">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Integrin alphaIIb beta3 &apos;outside-in&apos; signalling involves multiple proteins including SRC, SYK, SLP-76 and PLCgamma2. SRC is constitutively associated with the C-terminal tail of integrin beta 3. SYK is recruited to the beta3 tail and subsequently activated by SRC.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
