      <reaction metaid="metaid_993" id="reaction_418172" name="F2R binds ARRB2" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_70101">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Following receptor activation, PAR1 complexes with beta-arrestin. Beta-arrestins are adaptor proteins that play a central role in GPCR desensitization and internalization, and also act as scaffolds for the formation of signalling complexes that are independent of G-protein signalling.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
