      <reaction metaid="metaid_1005" id="reaction_202718" name="Integrin alphaLbeta2 (LFA-1) binds F11R (JAM-A)" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">JAM-A plays a key role in leukocyte transmigration and inflammatory extravasation. Transmigration of human leukocytes has been shown to involve heterophilic interactions of JAM-A with its integrin receptor LFA-1.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
