      <reaction metaid="metaid_1006" id="reaction_418200" name="SRC-1 bound to ARRB2 is not activated" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_70101">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Activated PAR1 can induce the formation of signalling complexes with a beta-arrestin scaffold. When beta-arrestin-1 is incorporated this leads to Src and subsequent ERK activation. In contrast, complexes containing beta-arrestin-2 do not lead to Src and ERK activation.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
