      <reaction metaid="metaid_1019" id="reaction_354087" name="Recruitment of GRB2 to p-PTK2" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_70101">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Phosphorylated tyrosine 925 in the FAT domain of PTK2/FAK creates a docking site for the SH2 domain of GRB2 and recruits the GRB2/SOS complex. PTK2 may use this mechanism to activate Ras and the MAP kinase pathway.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
