      <reaction metaid="metaid_1022" id="reaction_202724" name="P-selectin binds P-selectin ligand" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">PSGL-1 is expressed as a homodimer of two 120-kDa subunits that binds all four selectins, with the highest affinity for P-selectin, and is known to be constitutively expressed on the surface of platelets and most types of leukocytes. Besides playing a critical role in the inflammatory response by mediating leukocyte-leukocyte and leukocyte-endothelium interactions, PSGL-1 also participates in the hemostatic process by mediating leukocyte-platelet interactions.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
