      <reaction metaid="metaid_1032" id="reaction_984775" name="Kinesin-9 is a dimer" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_70101">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">KIF9 has the coiled-coil domain typical of the dimeric kinesins and is believed to function as a dimer.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
