      <reaction metaid="metaid_1035" id="reaction_204798" name="Interaction of Tie2 and p85 of PI3K" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The p85 subunit of phosphatidylinositol 3-kinase (PI3-kinase) associates with Tie2, most likely at phosphotyrosine 1102. This association leads on to the activation of Akt/PKB, a process linked to cell survival and antiapoptosis, and that may in part account for Tie2&apos;s role in vascular growth and maintenance.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
