      <reaction metaid="metaid_1052" id="reaction_390663" name="ADRA2A,B,C bind ADR,NAd" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_984">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Alpha-2 adrenoceptors couple with G protein alpha-i subtype which decreases adenylyl cyclase activity, thus reducing cAMP intracellular levels resulting in smooth muscle contraction. There are three alpha-2 subtypes in humans; 2A (Kobilka BK et al, 1987), 2B (Weinshank RL et al, 1990) and 2C (Hirasawa A et al, 1993).</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
