      <reaction metaid="metaid_1058" id="reaction_114558" name="Thrombin-activated PARs activate Gq" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_70101">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Activated PAR stimulates the G alpha (q) subunit to release GDP and bind GTP (which is present in much greater concentrations physiologically). This activation is required for Gq to participate in downstream signalling events.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
