      <reaction metaid="metaid_1061" id="reaction_372693" name="Phosphorylation of BCAR1 by SRC-PTK2 complex" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_70101">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">SH3-mediated binding of BCAR1/p130Cas to PTK2 is linked to enhanced tyrosine phosphorylation of BCAR1 at multiple sites. The Cas substrate domain contains 15 separate YxxP motifs, a main site of tyrosine phosphorylation on the BCAR1 molecule. Once phosphorylated, this domain serves as a docking site for the SH2 domains of CRK or NCK adaptor proteins that affect the downstream MAPK signalling pathway, resulting in cell survival and increased motility.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
