      <reaction metaid="metaid_1067" id="reaction_158893" name="alpha-2-antiplasmin + plasmin -&gt; alpha-2-antiplasmin:plasmin" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_984">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Plasmin binds the serpin alpha-2-antiplasmin, forming a stable and catalytically inactive complex. While several serpin proteins bind and inactivate plasmin in vitro, alpha-2-antiplasmin appears to be the only one with substantial plasmin-neutralizing activity in vivo (Moroi and Aoki 1976; Lijnen et al. 1987).</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
