      <reaction metaid="metaid_1070" id="reaction_204824" name="Interaction of Tie2 and Ang4" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_984">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Ang4 represents a third protein of the Ang family that binds to the Tie2 receptor. The mouse Ang3 and human Ang4 are interspecies orthologs. Ang4 acts as an activating ligand and induces phosphorylation in Tie2.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
