      <reaction metaid="metaid_1073" id="reaction_392852" name="Activated prostacyclin receptor binds G-protein Gs" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The human prostacyclin receptor (IP) and G-protein alpha (s) physically interact through contacts between the IP iLP1 domain and the C-terminal residues of the G alpha (s) protein.</p>
        </notes>
