      <reaction metaid="metaid_1074" id="reaction_204813" name="Interaction of Tie2 and Grb14" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Grb14 is also one of the signaling partners of Tie2. The SH2 domain of Grb2 mediates binding to Tie2. It binds residues Y816, Y1108 and Y1113 respectively, in the C-terminal tail region of Tie2/Tek.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
