      <reaction metaid="metaid_1078" id="reaction_997237" name="SH2B proteins bind JAK2" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_70101">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The SH2B family has 3 members sharing a common domain structure, including a dimerization domain, a pleckstrin homology (PH) region, and a SH2 domain. The SH2 domain binds phosphotyrosines of various signal-transducing proteins such as c-Kit, MPL, EpoR. All are able to bind JAK2 phosphorylated at Tyr-813 (Bersenev et al. 2008, Kurzer et al. 2004, 2006), inhibiting JAK2 proliferative signaling (Gery et al. 2009).</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
