      <reaction metaid="metaid_1082" id="reaction_202706" name="Integrin alpha4beta1 binds JAM2:JAM3" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Several key IgSF cell adhesion molecules engage integrin and in so doing impact on the multi-step paradigm of leukocyte emigration. The interaction between JAM2 (JAM-B) and Integrin alpha4beta1 (VLA-4) requires prior binding of JAM2 to JAM3 (JAM-C).</p>
        </notes>
