      <reaction metaid="metaid_1085" id="reaction_426223" name="Cation influx mediated by TRPC3/6/7" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_876">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">TRP channels are non-selectively permeable to cations, allowing enty into the cell via concentration gradients. All mammalian TRPCs require PLC for activation.</p>
        </notes>
