      <reaction metaid="metaid_1089" id="reaction_418442" name="PKG1 phosphorylates IRAG:IP3R1 inhibiting IP3-stimulated Ca2+ release" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_70101">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">IRAG, PKG1(cGKI), and IP3 receptor type 1 can be isolated as a complex in human platelets. Phosphorylation of IRAG by PKG1 inhibits IP3 receptor-mediated Ca2+ release, representing the primary mechanism by which NO suppresses platelet activation.</p>
        </notes>
