      <reaction metaid="metaid_1094" id="reaction_204549" name="Caveolin-1 binds Basigin" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_20699">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Stromal fibroblasts secrete multiple matrix metalloproteinases (MMP)1 that can promote tumor cell growth, survival, invasion, angiogenesis, and metastasis. Basigin on the surface of carcinoma cells, stimulates production of MMP-1 (interstitial collagenase), MMP-2 (gelatinase A), and MMP-3 (stromelysin). Basigin has been shown to co-immunoprecipitate with caveolin-1. The second Ig domain of Basigin is required for this association, which leads to decreased Besigin self-association on the cell surface. Therefore, caveolin-1 is a negative regulator of CD147 self-association, and its MMP-inducing activity.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
