      <reaction metaid="metaid_1102" id="reaction_9724753" name="PLG(20-810) binds anti-fibrinolytics" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_984">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The plasminogen inhibitors aminocaproic acid (Sun et al. 2002) and tranexamic acid (Sperzel and Huetter 2007, Cheng et al. 2014) can be administered to patients undergoing coronary artery bypass graft surgery to reduce bleeding.</p>
        </notes>
