      <reaction metaid="metaid_1113" id="reaction_210277" name="Interaction of PECAM-1 and SHP-1" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_70101">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The phosphorylation of two tandem tyrosine residues (Y663 and Y686) within the cytoplasmic domain of PECAM-1 is required for the downstream signalling events observed following PECAM-1 ligation. Both SH2 domains of SHP-1 are required in tandem to bind PECAM-1.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
