      <reaction metaid="metaid_1115" id="reaction_430076" name="GP1b-IX-V binds 14-3-3-zeta" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_70101">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The Gp1b-IX-V complex binds to 14-3-3-zeta, a scaffolding protein. The highly conserved cytoplasmic domain of GpIb alpha binds directly to dimeric 14-3-3 zeta adapter protein. Binding also involves regions of GpV, and is enhanced by phosphorylation of GP1b at Ser-609 or Ser-166 of Gp1b alpha and beta respectively. For Gp1b beta this phosphorylation is PKA-dependent.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
