      <reaction metaid="metaid_1123" id="reaction_140847" name="factor XIII cleaved tetramer + 2 Ca++ -&gt; factor XIIIa + 2 factor XIII B chain" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_984">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Once the A chains of the Factor XIII tetramer have been cleaved by thrombin, the complex dissociates, and the resulting A chain dimer binds Ca++ (one per peptide monomer) to form activated factor XIII (factor XIIIa).</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
