      <reaction metaid="metaid_1125" id="reaction_354073" name="Autophosphorylation of PTK2 at Y397" reversible="false" fast="false" compartment="compartment_70101">
        <notes>
          <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The co-localization of PTK2/FAK with integrins in focal adhesions and the actin cytoskeleton is essential for the activation and phosphorylation of PTK2/FAK. PTK2/FAK has six tyrosine phosphorylation sites and tyrosine 397 is the main auto-phosphorylation site present upstream of the kinase domain.</p>
        </notes>
        <annotation>
          <rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:vCard="http://www.w3.org/2001/vcard-rdf/3.0#" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:bqbiol="http://biomodels.net/biology-qualifiers/">
